<item>
            <title>[HIVE-28594] HS2 WebUI&apos;s LDAP authentication has security issues</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-28594</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the following commit, we noticed that HS2 wanted to add Ldap authentication function to WEBUI:&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/hive/commit/d87e2fccc3b0f30f7808cc33d73aae6f07644212#diff-b7bbe8545a21ec7d7e9cfe40ef66444789e332996aaa9e7f1430dbe4822a2c9cR4027&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/hive/commit/d87e2fccc3b0f30f7808cc33d73aae6f07644212#diff-b7bbe8545a21ec7d7e9cfe40ef66444789e332996aaa9e7f1430dbe4822a2c9cR4027&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the following code in LDAPAuthenticationFilter seems to have security issues:&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/hive/blob/d87e2fccc3b0f30f7808cc33d73aae6f07644212/service/src/java/org/apache/hive/service/servlet/LDAPAuthenticationFilter.java#L52&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/hive/blob/d87e2fccc3b0f30f7808cc33d73aae6f07644212/service/src/java/org/apache/hive/service/servlet/LDAPAuthenticationFilter.java#L52&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13072473/13072473_image-20241025124321373.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here,&#160;&lt;tt&gt;request.getRequestURI()&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;is used to obtain the access URI and&#160;&lt;tt&gt;endswith&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;is used to determine the current access route.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, for this writing, attackers can use SEMICOLON to forge a URI suffix, for example:&#160;&lt;tt&gt;/hiveserver2.jsp;login&lt;/tt&gt;, and this causes permission escape.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
